00:11:47,875 --> 00:11:49,458
imagine Buddha's heartbreak

285
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:50,500
watching his own cousin

286
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:52,291
lead away hundreds of disciples

287
00:11:52,375 --> 00:11:54,500
claiming to be the real Buddhist leader

288
00:11:54,625 --> 00:11:57,666
but Buddha doesn't argue doesn't fight back

289
00:11:58,083 --> 00:11:59,958
he simply continues teaching

290
00:12:00,208 --> 00:12:01,625
demonstrating through actions

291
00:12:01,625 --> 00:12:03,458
what true Buddhism looks like

292
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:06,166
and his silence speaks louder than any argument

293
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:09,541
within weeks those 500 monks notice something

294
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:11,833
without Buddha around to compete with

295
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:15,000
Devadatta shows his true nature controlling

296
00:12:15,041 --> 00:12:18,000
demanding obsessed with rules and punishment

297
00:12:18,375 --> 00:12:20,708
the pure Buddhism Devadatta promised

298
00:12:20,958 --> 00:12:22,833
it turns into a cult of fear

299
00:12:23,416 --> 00:12:26,000
question him and you're punished

300
00:12:26,666 --> 00:12:29,083
compassion gets replaced by control

301
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:33,291
one by one the monks return to Buddha apologizing

302
00:12:33,291 --> 00:12:36,750
asking for forgiveness Buddha welcomes them back

303
00:12:36,791 --> 00:12:38,875
no questions no punishments

304
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:39,958
no lectures

305
00:12:40,666 --> 00:12:42,250
just welcome home

306
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:46,250
but for Devadatta watching his followers abandon him

307
00:12:46,291 --> 00:12:48,500
this realization comes too late

308
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:51,958
the karma he's been building is about to explode

309
00:12:56,541 --> 00:12:57,625
Devadatta's failed at everything

310
00:12:58,541 --> 00:13:00,333
murder conspiracy

311
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:03,125
community splitting he's alone abandoned

312
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:04,458
exposed as a fraud

313
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:06,791
but the universe isn't done with him yet

314
00:13:07,166 --> 00:13:08,875
according to Buddhist teachings

315
00:13:08,875 --> 00:13:11,291
some actions create Änantariya karma

316
00:13:11,375 --> 00:13:13,083
immediate consequences

317
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:16,791
attacking an awakened being

318
00:13:17,083 --> 00:13:18,333
that's one of them

319
00:13:18,666 --> 00:13:21,041
and Devadatta was about to find out why

320
00:13:22,083 --> 00:13:23,625
strange things start happening

321
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:25,875
Devadata develops a mysterious illness

322
00:13:26,125 --> 00:13:28,375
his body breaking down not from disease

323
00:13:28,375 --> 00:13:31,041
but like his own hatred is eating him from the inside

324
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,958
his skin becomes covered in painful boils

325
00:13:33,958 --> 00:13:37,208
his strength fails he's constantly feverish

326
00:13:37,666 --> 00:13:39,166
the physical symptoms are nothing

327
00:13:39,166 --> 00:13:40,833
compared to what's happening mentally

328
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:42,541
he starts having nightmares

329
00:13:42,541 --> 00:13:44,708
where he's chased by the very elephants and boulders

330
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:47,500
he used against Buddha he can't sleep

331
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,625
can't eat can't find peace

332
00:13:50,166 --> 00:13:52,708
people report supernatural events around him

333
00:13:52,708 --> 00:13:54,500
ground shaking when he walks

334
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:58,000
animals fleeing plants withering in his presence

335
00:13:58,541 --> 00:14:01,416
it's like the natural world is rejecting him

336
00:14:01,791 --> 00:14:04,791
but Buddha knowing everything Devadatta has done

337
00:14:04,916 --> 00:14:06,416
does something incredible

338
00:14:06,625 --> 00:14:08,333
he visits his dying cousin

339
00:14:08,791 --> 00:14:11,291
the man Devadatta tried to murder three times

340
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:12,041
walks into the room

341
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:14,708
where his cousin is being consumed by his own karma

342
00:14:15,291 --> 00:14:17,791
seeing Buddha approach Devadatta panics

343
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:19,333
he knows he's dying

344
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:21,000
and his last chance for redemption is

345
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,791
standing right there he tries to get up

346
00:14:23,791 --> 00:14:25,791
tries to bow but his body's too weak

347
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,458
he manages to raise his hands

348
00:14:27,458 --> 00:14:29,083
and whispers with his dying breath

349
00:14:29,791 --> 00:14:31,500
I take refuge in Buddha

350
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:34,958
Buddha places his hand on Devadatta's forehead

351
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:37,666
your recognition of truth creates merit

352
00:14:37,791 --> 00:14:39,583
you are not completely lost

353
00:14:41,083 --> 00:14:42,875
Devadatta dies right there

354
00:14:42,875 --> 00:14:44,583
but with that final surrender

355
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:46,541
he creates just enough positive karma

356
00:14:46,541 --> 00:14:48,625
to avoid the worst possible rebirth

357
00:14:49,666 --> 00:14:51,375
but his death isn't quiet

358
00:14:51,583 --> 00:14:52,916
the ancient texts say

359
00:14:52,916 --> 00:14:54,750
the earth cracked open beneath him

360
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:57,583
thunder boomed flames erupted

361
00:14:57,833 --> 00:15:00,083
it was like nature itself cried out

362
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:02,875
this is what happens when love turns to hate

363
00:15:03,916 --> 00:15:05,708
Buddha's reaction to watching his cousin

364
00:15:05,708 --> 00:15:08,500
swallowed by the earth not Celebration

365
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:12,875
not vindication grief pure heartbroken grief

366
00:15:14,208 --> 00:15:15,416
he remembers the little boy

367
00:15:15,416 --> 00:15:17,333
who played with him in palace court yards

368
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:20,041
taught him archery shared his royal childhood

369
00:15:20,958 --> 00:15:23,125
somewhere inside that twisted man

370
00:15:23,375 --> 00:15:25,625
that innocent child still existed

371
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:28,500
Buddha later tells his disciples

372
00:15:28,583 --> 00:15:32,208
Devadatta was consumed by the three poisons greed

373
00:15:32,208 --> 00:15:35,916
hatred and delusion but even in his final moment

374
00:15:35,916 --> 00:15:38,625
he showed that awakening is possible for everyone

375
00:15:39,666 --> 00:15:41,750
then Buddha says something that changes everything

376
00:15:42,083 --> 00:15:45,125
Devadatta was my teacher as much as I was his

377
00:15:45,541 --> 00:15:48,166
he taught me compassion by showing me hatred

378
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:50,083
patience by testing mine

379
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:52,750
forgiveness by doing the unforgivable

380
00:15:57,166 --> 00:16:00,208
so what does this 2,500 year old family drama

381
00:16:00,208 --> 00:16:02,541
teach us about dealing with toxic people today

382
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,541
first toxic people aren't born evil

383
00:16:06,791 --> 00:16:09,208
Devadatta was consumed by the 3 poisons

384
00:16:09,541 --> 00:16:12,083
greed for power hatred from jealousy

385
00:16:12,083 --> 00:16:14,083
and delusion about his own righteousness

386
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:16,791
think about your own toxic family members

387
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,458
aren't they usually driven by these same forces

388
00:16:20,291 --> 00:16:23,750
second fighting toxic people only makes them more toxic

389
00:16:24,125 --> 00:16:26,291
every time Buddha could have retaliated

390
00:16:26,291 --> 00:16:28,208
he chose compassion instead

391
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:31,000
that choice led to Devadatta's self destruction

392
00:16:31,291 --> 00:16:33,000
Buddha didn't defeat his enemy

393
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,958
his enemy defeated himself

394
00:16:36,291 --> 00:16:38,083
what would happen if you stopped fighting back

395
00:16:38,083 --> 00:16:39,625
against your toxic relatives

396
00:16:40,708 --> 00:16:43,708
third your worst enemies can be your greatest teachers

397
00:16:44,208 --> 00:16:45,875
Buddha said Devadatta forced him to

398
00:16:45,875 --> 00:16:48,000
practice compassion at the highest level

399
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:51,208
your toxic family members aren't just obstacles

400
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:53,916
they're your training ground for becoming more patient

401
00:16:53,958 --> 00:16:56,208
forgiving and wise

402
00:16:57,333 --> 00:17:00,708
fourth everyone has potential for redemption

403
00:17:01,458 --> 00:17:03,833
even Devadatta in his final breath

404
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:06,416
found enough light to save himself from the worst fate

405
00:17:07,041 --> 00:17:08,666
nobody is beyond hope

406
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:11,833
finally you can't control others actions

407
00:17:11,875 --> 00:17:13,291
only your responses

408
00:17:13,916 --> 00:17:16,208
Buddha couldn't stop the assassination attempts

409
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:17,875
but he could choose how to respond

410
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:19,875
with love instead of revenge

411
00:17:20,583 --> 00:17:22,375
that choice made all the difference

412
00:17:23,583 --> 00:17:25,125
remember what the Buddha said

413
00:17:25,416 --> 00:17:27,291
hatred does not cease by hatred

414
00:17:27,291 --> 00:17:30,666
but only by love that wasn't just a line

415
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:33,750
he lived it and so can we

416
00:17:35,666 --> 00:17:37,500
next time someone close betrays you

417
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,041
remember Buddha and Devadatta

418
00:17:39,291 --> 00:17:41,541
your response not their action

419
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:43,125
determines who you become

420
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:45,750
will you let their poison consume you

421
00:17:45,750 --> 00:17:48,208
or will you choose the path that sets you free

422
00:17:48,875 --> 00:17:50,958
choose compassion not because they deserve it

423
00:17:50,958 --> 00:17:52,375
but because you do

424
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:55,125
you deserve freedom from hatred's poison

425
